(29, 2981, 'Legislacion Espanola de suelos contaminados: Nueva ley de residuos y\r\nsuelos contaminados', 'es', 'Legislacion Española de contaminated soils: new law on waste and\r\ncontaminated soils', 'en', 'Spanish legislation for contaminated soils: new law on waste and\r\ncontaminated soils', 23, 6, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(30, 2981, 'La presentación se centra en la legislación desarrollada en materia de suelos contaminados en España, abordando la nueva Ley de residuos y suelos contaminados, recientemente aprobada en julio y el Real Decreto 9/2005.', 'es', 'The presentation focuses on the legislation developed in the field of contaminated soils in Spain, dealing with the new law of waste and contaminated soils, recently approved in July and the Royal Decree 9/2005.', 'en', 'The presentation focuses on the legislation developed for covering contaminated soils in Spain, dealing with the new law of waste and contaminated soils, recently approved in July and the Royal Decree 9/2005.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(31, 2981, 'Legislacion', 'es', 'Legislation', 'en', 'Legislation', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(32, 2981, 'suelos contaminados', 'es', 'contaminated soils', 'en', 'contaminated soils', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(33, 2983, 'Directiva ue de suelos: ¿Sentar las bases para Conseguir materia organica de calidad?', 'es', 'Directive EU of soils: do the groundwork to get quality organic matter?', 'en', 'EU directive for soils: Paving the way to get quality organic matter?', 23, 6, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(34, 2983, '“Los suelos sanos producen cultivos saludables que promueven la salud en los animales y en la gente” –esto es lo que remarcan los principios de la agricultura ecológica de IFOAM. Por ello, debemos procurar que se aplique una buena política de suelos en la UE La propuesta de Directiva de Suelos está atascada en los pasillos del Consejo, debido a que unos pocos estados miembros están bloqueando que se avance en su aprobación.', 'es', '', 'en', '&quot;Healthy soils produce healthy crops that promote health in animals and people&quot; - this is what stresses the principles of ecological agriculture of IFOAM. For this reason, we must try to apply good soil policy in the EU, the proposal for a directive on soil is stuck in the Council halls, due to the fact that a few Member States are blocking progress in their approval.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(35, 2983, 'directiva', 'es', 'Directive', 'en', 'Directive', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(36, 2983, 'materia organica', 'es', 'organic matter', 'en', 'organic matter', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(37, 2984, 'Propuesta de directiva ue de suelos: Estado de la cuestion', 'es', 'Proposal for a directive EU of soils: State of the art', 'en', 'Proposal for an EU directive for soils: State of the art', 23, 6, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(38, 2984, 'La Comisión pretende frenar con esa propuesta, el aumento de acciones contra el suelo, la restauración de áreas degradadas, el incremento de la conciencia pública sobre los suelos y conseguir una mayor sinergia entre los distintos ámbitos políticos. También establece inventarios nacionales de los sitios contaminados y la naturaleza flexible de la Directiva, respetando la gran variabilidad de uso de la naturaleza, el uso del suelo y la tierra en los Estados miembros. En la presentación se explica de forma detallada el estado de las propuestas y los avances que se prevén.', 'es', 'The Commission intends to stop with this proposal, the increase in actions on the ground, the restoration of degraded areas, the increase in public awareness of the soils and achieve a greater synergy between the different policy areas. It also establishes a national inventory of contaminated sites and the flexible nature of the directive, respecting the great variability of use of nature, the use of soil and land in the Member States. The presentation explains in detail the status of the proposals and the progress is expected.', 'en', 'The Commission intends to stop with this proposal the increased actions on the soil, the restoration of degraded areas, the increase in public awareness of the soils and achieve a greater synergy between the different policy areas. It also establishes a national inventory of contaminated sites and the flexible nature of the directive, respecting the great variability of use of nature, the use of soil and land in the Member States. The presentation explains in detail the status of the proposals and the expected progress.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(39, 2984, 'soil health', 'en', 'la salud del suelo', 'es', 'la salud del suelo', 23, 35, 1, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(40, 2984, 'soil issue', 'en', 'Cuestión del suelo', 'es', 'Cuestión del suelo', 23, 35, 1, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(41, 2984, 'legislation', 'en', 'La legislación', 'es', 'La legislación', 23, 35, 1, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(42, 2986, 'Agricultura y erosion del suelo', 'es', 'Agriculture and soil erosion', 'en', 'Agriculture and soil erosion', 23, 6, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(43, 2986, 'Se realiza una revisión del estado de la cuestión de la erosión en suelos agrícolas en España. Para ello se consultan la base bibliográfica fundamental y se aporta información sobre las mediciones y estimaciones de la erosión en España. Se comparan los resultados de los estudios en suelos forestales con los obtenidos en los suelos agrícolas y se llega a la conclusión de que son éstos últimos los suelos que mayores pérdidas de suelo y aguas presentan. También se apuntan las medidas a tomar para reducir estas pérdidas de suelo.', 'es', 'He is a review of the status of the question of the erosion in agricultural soils in Spain. So referring to the bibliographic basis and provides information about the measurements and estimates of erosion in Spain. Comparing the results of studies on forest land with those obtained in the agricultural soils and reach the conclusion that are latter soils presenting greater losses of soil and water. Also point the measures to take to reduce these losses of soil.', 'en', 'This is a review of the status of the status of the erosion in agricultural soils in Spain. It refers to a bibliographic basis and provides information about the measurements and estimates of erosion in Spain. It compares the results of studies on forest land with those obtained in the agricultural soils and reaches the conclusion that are latter soils presenting greater losses of soil and water. The paper also points the measures to be taken to reduce these losses of soil.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(44, 2986, 'agricultura', 'es', 'Agriculture', 'en', 'Agriculture', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(45, 2986, 'aguas', 'es', 'waters', 'en', 'water', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(46, 2986, 'erosión', 'es', 'erosion', 'en', 'erosion', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(47, 2986, 'suelos', 'es', 'soils', 'en', 'soils', 23, 35, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(48, 2987, 'Ganaderia ecologica y sostenibilidad de los sistemas agrosilvopastoriles', 'es', 'Animal husbandry ecological and sustainability of agrosilvopastoral systems', 'en', 'Organic animal husbandry and sustainability of agroforestry systems', 23, 6, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
(49, 2987, 'La ganadería ecológica es el mejor instrumento que tiene las administraciones públicas para un desarrollo rural competitivo, con múltiples beneficios para los agrosilvosistemas pastorales. \r\nA) Mejora la fertilidad del suelo y banco de semillas gracias al redileo/majadeo, aumenta la diversidad biológica en términos de biomasa microbiana e invertebrada (moduladora del control biológico natural), junto a los recursos cinegéticos (perdiz roja, conejo, liebre, ciervo y corzo).\r\nB). Previene los incendios forestales por el ajuste de la carga ganadera y presión de pastoreo, que conlleva a un control eficaz de la biomasa inflamable y a una regeneración uniforme del monte. \r\nC) Restaura el paisaje rural al conferir una mayor autonomía biológica y funcional. D)\r\nMitiga el cambio climático al liberase menos gases con efecto invernadero debido al uso del estiércol y técnicas bioecológicas de la cría. \r\nE) Preserva la cultura agraria, aumenta la demografía rural y favorece la integración de la unidad familiar en el medio rural. \r\nF) Potencia el mercado local mediante un sistema agroalimentario más sustentable, desarrolla un consumo responsable de alta calidad y seguridad alimentaria para la sociedad.', 'es', 'Organic livestock is the best instrument that has public administrations for a competitive rural development, with multiple benefits for the pastoral agrosilvosistemas. \r\nA) improving the fertility of soil and seed thanks to the redileo Bank / I majadeo, increases biological diversity in terms of microbial and invertebrate biomass (natural biological control modulator), along with the hunting resources (red-legged Partridge, rabbit, Hare, deer and Roe deer).\r\n(B). prevent forest fires by setting the stocking density and grazing pressure, which leads to effective control of flammable biomass and a uniform regeneration of del monte. \r\n(C) restore the countryside to confer greater biological and functional autonomy. D)\r\nMitigating climate change to the release less greenhouse gases due to the use of manure and technical emphasis of breeding. \r\n(E) preserves the agrarian culture, increases rural demographics and favours the integration of the family unit in the rural environment. \r\nF) power the local market through a more sustainable food system, develops a responsible consumption of high quality and food security for society.', 'en', 'Organic livestock is the major instrument that has public administrations for a competitive rural development, with multiple benefits for the pastoral agroforestry systems. \r\nA) improving the fertility of soil and seed thanks to the redileo Bank / I majadeo, increases biological diversity in terms of microbial and invertebrate biomass (natural biological control modulator), along with the hunting resources (red-legged partridge, rabbit, hare, deer and Roe deer).\r\n(B). prevents forest fires by setting the stocking density and grazing pressure, which leads to effective control of flammable biomass and a uniform regeneration of the mountain. \r\n(C) restore the countryside to confer greater biological and functional autonomy. \r\n(D) Mitigating climate change to the release less greenhouse gases due to the use of manure and technical emphasis of breeding. \r\n(E) preserves the agrarian culture, increases rural demographics and favours the integration of the family unit in the rural environment. \r\n(F) powers the local market through a more sustainable food system, develops a responsible consumption of high quality and food security for society.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-07-02', NULL),
