(130, 3123, 'Numerosos olivares cultivados en el área mediterránea se sitúan en laderas de pendientes moderadas\r\na altas. En este contexto, las cubiertas son estratégicas para evitar la erosión, y su uso se está\r\nimponiendo entre los olivareros ecológicos. Sin embargo, también puede tener un efecto adverso\r\nsobre la producción de aceituna, principalmente debido al consumo de agua. Dado que el manejo\r\ndifiere enormemente entre olivareros ecológicos en dos aspectos esenciales: el uso de la vegetación\r\nespontánea o de una cubierta sembrada (generalmente, veza); y la forma de control (con incorporación\r\nde la cubierta mediante el pase de cultivador u otro apero, o con desbrozadora y abandono de\r\nlos restos en superficie), es necesario evaluar el efecto de las distintas estrategias de manejo sobre\r\nel suelo, el agua disponible para el cultivo y la biodiversidad vegetal.\r\nConocer el impacto de las distintas estrategias es el objetivo de este ensayo de seis años en\r\nDeifontes (Granada), que compara, en un diseño en bloques al azar de tres tratamientos con cuatro\r\nrepeticiones, el efecto de una cubierta de veza manejada con desbrozadora con otra de la misma\r\ncomposición pero incorporada mediante cultivador, y otra de vegetación natural, también incorporada,\r\nque suele ser la opción más frecuente entre olivareros ecológicos. En esta comunicación se\r\nrecoge el efecto de los diferentes manejos sobre la flora silvestre, el contenido del agua y la fertilidad\r\nedáfica.', 'es', 'Numerous olive groves grown in the Mediterranean area are situated on slopes of moderate slopes\r\nto high. In this context, the covers are strategic to prevent erosion, and their use is\r\nbe imposed between the ecological activists. However, you can also have an adverse effect\r\non the production of olives, mainly due to the consumption of water. Given that the management\r\ndiffers greatly between olive green in two essential aspects: the use of vegetation\r\nspontaneous or a cover sown (usually, vetch); and the form control (with addition\r\ncover pass cultivator or other apéro, or brush cutter and abandonment of\r\nthe remains on surface), it is necessary to assess the effect of the different management strategies on\r\nthe soil, the water available for farming and plant biodiversity.\r\nAwareness of the impact of different strategies is the goal of this six-year trial in\r\nDeifontes (Granada), comparing, on a block design at random from three treatments with four\r\nrepetitions, the effect of a cover of vetch handled brushcutter with another of the same\r\ncomposition but incorporated by grower, and other natural vegetation, also incorporated,\r\nIt tends to be the most frequent choice among olive green. In this communication are\r\nIt includes the effect of different managements on the wild flora, the water content and fertility\r\nsoil.', 'en', 'Numerous olive groves grown in the Mediterranean area are situated on slopes of moderate to high slopes. In this context, the covers are strategic to prevent erosion, and their use is be imposed between the ecological activists. However, this can also have an adverse effect on the production of olives, mainly due to the consumption of water. Given that the management\r\ndiffers greatly between green olive in two essential aspects: the use of spontaneous vegetation or a cover sown (usually, vetch); and the form control (with additional cover pass cultivator or other apéro, or brush cutter and abandonment of the remains on surface), it is necessary to assess the effect of the different management strategies on the soil, the water available for farming and plant biodiversity. Awareness of the impact of different strategies is the goal of this six-year trial in Deifontes (Granada), comparing, on a block design at random from three treatments with four repetitions, the effect of a cover of vetch handled brush cutter with another of the same composition but incorporated by grower, and other natural vegetation, also incorporated, It tends to be the most frequent choice among olive green. \r\n\r\nIn this communication are included the effects of different managements on the wild flora, the water content and soil fertility soil.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-09-03', NULL),
