(165, 3131, 'Los nematodos del género Globodera son una plaga muy importante en el cultivo de papa en Canarias. El control químico es poco efectivo, costoso y está restringido por la normativa comunitaria vigente debido a sus efectos ambientales y sobre la salud humana. Como alternativa de manejo del nematodo se ha planteado inducir de la eclosión de los quistes en ausencia del hospedero, para que los juveniles emergidos mueran por falta de alimento. En este trabajo se ensayó el efecto de macerado de ramas de papa, macerado de ramas de tomate, exudados radiculares de tomate y purines de oveja, además del nematicida habitual y un testigo, sobre la eclosión de quistes en macetas. Para ello, se comparó el número de quistes antes y después de aplicar los tratamientos. Posteriormente se cultivó papa en estas macetas, evaluándose el número de quistes al final del cultivo y la producción de papa. Todos los tratamientos ensayados disminuyeron significativamente el número de quistes respecto al\r\ntestigo, existiendo diferencias significativas a favor de los tratamientos con macerados vegetales frente al resto. Sin embargo, tras el cultivo de papa, las poblaciones del nematodo recuperaron niveles similares a los iniciales en todos los casos. Esto demuestra la inefectividad del nematicida habitual, así como de una única aplicación de macerados, aunque éstos podrían\r\nincrementar su efectividad con aplicaciones reiteradas. No se observó relación entre el número de quistes y la producción de papa, aspecto que debería estudiarse en condiciones de campo para determinar la necesidad real de realizar tratamientos.', 'es', 'Nematodes of the genus Globodera are a very important pest in the cultivation of potatoes in the Canary Islands. Chemical control is to be effective, expensive and is restricted by Community legislation because of their environmental effects and human health. As an alternative to the nematode management has been raised to induce hatching of cysts in the absence of the host, so emerged juveniles die for lack of food. In this work were tested the effect of branches of Pope, maceration of branches of tomato, marinated root exudates from tomato and slurry of sheep, in addition to the usual nematicide and a witness, about the emergence of cysts in pots. To do this, comparing the number of cysts before and after applying the treatments. Later Pope was cultivated in these pots, assessing the number of cysts at the end of the crop and potato production. All the tested treatments significantly decreased the number of cysts on the\r\nwitness, there are significant differences in favor of treatments with marinated vegetables compared to the rest. However, after the potato crop, the nematode populations recovered levels similar to the initials in all cases. This demonstrates the ineffectiveness of the usual nematicide, as well as a single application of macerated, although these could\r\nincrease your effectiveness with repeated applications. Relationship between the number of cysts and potato production, aspect that should be studied under field conditions to determine the real need for treatments were observed.', 'en', 'Nematodes of the genus Globodera are a very important pest in the cultivation of potatoes in the Canary Islands. Chemical control is to be effective, expensive and is restricted by Community legislation because of their effects on environment and human health. As an alternative to the nematode management has been raised to induce hatching of cysts in the absence of the host, so emerged juveniles die of lack of food. In this work  the effect of branches of Pope, maceration of branches of tomato, marinated root exudates from tomato and slurry of sheep, in addition to the usual nematicide and a witness were tested, for the emergence of cysts in pots. To do this,the number of cysts was compared before and after applying the treatments. Later Pope was cultivated in these pots, assessing the number of cysts at the end of the crop and potato production. All the tested treatments significantly decreased the number of cysts on the witness, there are significant differences in favor of treatments with marinated vegetables compared to the rest. However, after the potato crop, the nematode populations recovered levels similar to the initials in all cases. This demonstrates the ineffectiveness of the usual nematicide, as well as a single application of macerated, although these could increase their effectiveness with repeated applications. Relationship between the number of cysts and potato production, is an aspect that should be studied under field conditions to determine the real need for treatments were observed.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-09-03', NULL),
