(169, 3132, 'Reflexiones sobre el uso de la diversidad vegetal en la conversión ecológica del olivar tradicional mecanizable de Andalucía', 'es', 'Reflections on the use of plant biodiversity in the ecological conversion of machineable traditional olive groves in Andalusia', 'en', 'Reflections on the use of plant biodiversity in the organic conversion of machineable traditional olive groves in Andalusia', 23, 6, 2, '2013-09-03', NULL),
(170, 3132, 'La conversión ecológica del olivar tradicional mecanizable es una de las principales medidas para afrontar a corto plazo el mantenimiento de la rentabilidad económica de este importante agroecosistema en algunas zonas de Andalucía. Para ello se hace imprescindible un uso integrado y racional de la diversidad vegetal que además permita la sostenibilidad del sistema abordando alguno de sus desequilibrios. Eso debería hacerse mediante medidas relativamente fáciles de aplicar y, sobre todo, a bajo coste, basadas en la implantación de diversas comunidades vegetales en los diferentes ambientes y situaciones de la explotación, para así evitar la pérdida de la fertilidad y otros procesos de degradación de los suelos, y aumentar la biodiversidad.\r\nEn este proceso de conversión se propone el uso de diferentes especies vegetales de gran adaptación al agroecosistema del olivar orientadas en tres direcciones diferentes: \r\na) el establecimiento de cubiertas en las calles con gramíneas para el control de la erosión, de crucíferas y mezclas de semillas de dicotiledóneas, para el incremento de la biodiversidad edáfica, y el incremento de la entomofauna auxiliar dentro del cultivo, respectivamente; \r\nb) la recuperación de zonas improductivas mediante la instalación de comunidades de herbáceas vivaces en zonas de paso de maquinaria y leñosas en zonas limítrofes; y \r\nc) la instalación de cubiertas de herbáceas perennes en zonas de vaguada, surcos y cabecera de cárcavas, y arbustivas en cárcavas ya formadas.\r\n\r\nEn esta comunicación se presentan, con el objetivo de discutirlos, una serie de criterios básicos de decisión para la aplicación ordenada de esas medidas mediante un plan genérico de trabajo que se adapte a las diferentes realidades ambientales de distintos olivares. A modo de ejemplo,\r\nse muestra en una finca tipo del Valle del Guadalquivir de 50 años de edad a un marco de 8x8 m a 2-3 pies, sobre un suelo franco arcilloso con riego deficitario y pendientes moderadas.', 'es', 'Ecological conversion of machineable traditional olive groves is one of the main measures to address short term maintaining the profitability of this important agro-ecosystem in some areas of Andalusia. For this it is essential to an integrated and rational use of plant diversity that also allow the sustainability of the system by addressing one of its imbalances. That should be relatively easy to apply measures and, above all, a low-cost, based on the implementation of different plant communities in different environments and situations of exploitation, to prevent the loss of fertility and other processes of soil degradation, and increasing biodiversity.\r\nThis conversion process proposes the use of different species of great adaptation to the agro-ecosystem of the olive grove oriented in three different directions: to) the establishment of covers in the streets with grasses for the control of erosion, cruciferous and mixtures of seeds of dicots, for the increase of soil biodiversity, and the increase of the entomofauna auxiliary within the culturerespectively; \r\n(b) the recovery of unproductive areas through the installation of communities of herbaceous perennials in zones of machinery and Woody in neighbouring areas; and (c) the installation of covers of herbaceous perennial in zones of trough, furrows and gullies header, and shrubs in already formed gullies.\r\n\r\nIn this communication occur, in order to discuss them, a number of basic criteria of decision for the orderly implementation of such measures through a generic work plan that adapts to the different environmental realities of different olive groves. By way of example,\r\nshown in a property type from the Valley of the Guadalquivir from 50 years of age to a frame of 8 x 8 m to 2-3 feet, on a clay loam soil with irrigation deficit and moderate slopes.', 'en', 'Organic conversion of machineable traditional olive groves is one of the main measures to short term address the maintaining of the profitability of this important agro-ecosystem in some areas of Andalusia. For this it is essential to an integrated and rational use of plant diversity that also allows the sustainability of the system by addressing one of its imbalances. That should be relatively easy to apply measures and, above all, a low-cost, based on the implementation of different plant communities in different environments and situations of exploitation, to prevent the loss of fertility and other processes of soil degradation, and increasing biodiversity.\r\nThis conversion process proposes the use of different species of great adaptation to the agro-ecosystem of the olive grove oriented in three different directions: to) the establishment of covers in the streets with grasses for the control of erosion, cruciferous and mixtures of seeds of dicots, for the increase of soil biodiversity, and the increase of the entomofauna auxiliary within the culturerespectively; (b) the recovery of unproductive areas through the installation of communities of herbaceous perennials in zones of machinery and Woody in neighbouring areas; and (c) the installation of covers of herbaceous perennial in zones of trough, furrows and gullies header, and shrubs in already formed gullies.\r\n\r\nIn this communication, in order to discuss them, a number of basic criteria are presented for deciding for the orderly implementation of such measures through a generic work plan that adapts to the different environmental realities of different olive groves. As an example, shown in a property type from the Valley of the Guadalquivir from 50 years of age to a frame of 8 x 8 m to 2-3 feet, on a clay loam soil with irrigation deficit and moderate slopes.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-09-03', NULL),
