(456, 3674, 'Pratiques culturales en viticulture en 2010 : Les viticulteurs bio adaptent leurs pratiques culturales', 'fi', 'Pratiques culturales en viticulture en 2010: Les pratiques culturales adaptent leurs in viticulteurs bio', 'en', 'Cultural practices in viticulture in 2010: Organic growers adapt their farming practices', 89, 6, 2, '2013-11-08', NULL),
(457, 3674, 'Sur le bassin viticole Val de Loire, un peu moins de 7% des surfaces sont conduites en AB, mais leur nombre progresse. Les viticulteurs biologiques diffèrent des conventionnels dans leurs pratiques, en général plus diversifiées. L’enherbement total des parcelles est deux fois plus présent chez les viticulteurs bio de ce bassin. Ils recourent fortement au désherbage mécanique ou thermique pour plus de 97 % des surfaces (contre 15 % des surfaces en conventionnel). Au moins deux désherbages ont lieu en bio par campagne sur les parcelles. Les traitements fongicides bio sont plus fréquents (en 2010, en moyenne 14 traitements bio contre 11 en conventionnel), de même que les travaux en vert (épamprage, effeuillage ou encore éclaircissage). Les rendements bio sont inférieurs (de 25% en 2010) par rapport au conventionnel, mais les prix du vin bio sont plus élevés. A noter que les vignes bio sont essentiellement valorisées en AOP.', 'fr', 'On the Val de Loire wine basin, a little less than 7% of the surfaces are conducted in AB, but their number is progressing. Organic growers differ from conventional in their practices, in general more diverse. Total weediness of the plots is twice as present in the organic growers of this basin. They use highly mechanical or thermal weed control for more than 97% of the surfaces (against 15% of conventional surfaces). At least two weeding takes place in bio by campaign on the plots. Bio fungicide treatments are more frequent (in 2010, averaging 14 bio 11 conventional treatments), as well as the work in green (Crown suckering, thinning or thinning). Organic yields are lower (from 25% in 2010) compared to the conventional, but bio wine prices are higher. Note that organic vineyards are essentially valued PDO.', 'en', 'On the Val de Loire wine basin, a little less than 7% of the surfaces are conducted in AB, but their number is progressing. Organic growers differ from conventional in their practices, in general more diverse. Total weediness of the plots is twice as present in the organic growers of this basin. They use highly mechanical or thermal weed control for more than 97% of the surfaces (against 15% of conventional surfaces). At least two weeding takes place in bio by campaign on the plots. Bio fungicide treatments are more frequent (in 2010, averaging 14 bio 11 conventional treatments), as well as the work in green (Crown suckering, thinning or thinning). Organic yields are lower (from 25% in 2010) compared to the conventional, but bio wine prices are higher. Note that organic vineyards are essentially valued PDO.', 89, 8, 2, '2013-11-08', NULL),
