(474, 3675, 'Des prairies permanentes, unique ressource d''un système laitier biologique en Lorraine', 'fr', 'Permanent pasture, unique resource of a biological dairy system in Lorraine', 'en', 'Permanent pasture, unique resource of a biological dairy system in Lorraine', 89, 6, 2, '2013-11-08', NULL),
(475, 3675, 'Ce document a été réalisé lors des 17èmes journées 3R (Rencontres Recherches Ruminants), en 2010. Dans les exploitations agricoles, la recherche d’économie d’intrants représente un enjeu économique mais également socio-écologique. Dans ce contexte, un prototype de système bovin laitier herbager simple et autonome, sur une surface exclusivement conduite en prairies permanentes, a été testé sur la station expérimentale INRA ASTER-Mirecourt. La sécurisation du système repose ici sur des stocks de fourrages importants, valorisés notamment via une maximisation du pâturage, et sur le groupement des vêlages en fin d’hiver pour parfaire l’équilibre entre ressources alimentaires disponibles et besoins du troupeau. Ce second point reste à optimiser pour permettre plus de souplesse en cas d’aléas climatiques.', 'fr', 'This document has been produced during the 17th 3R (meetings research Ruminants), in 2010. In farms, searching for saving input represents a challenge economic but also ecological. In this context, a prototype system dairy cattle grazier simple and autonomous, on a surface exclusively conducted in permanent pasture, has been tested on the station experimental INRA ASTER-Mirecourt. The secure system is here based on stocks of important fodder, valued particularly through maximization of the pasture, and the grouping of the calvings late winter to perfect the balance between food availability and needs of the herd. This second point remains to optimize to allow more flexibility in the event of climatic hazards.', 'en', 'This document has been produced during the 17th 3R (meetings research Ruminants), in 2010. On farms, seeking input savings represents an economic but also socio-ecological issue. In this context, a prototype system dairy cattle grazier simple and autonomous, on a surface exclusively conducted in permanent pasture, has been tested on the station experimental INRA ASTER-Mirecourt. The secure system is here based on stocks of important fodder, valued particularly through maximization of the pasture, and the grouping of the calvings late winter to perfect the balance between food availability and needs of the herd. This second point remains to optimize to allow more flexibility in the event of climatic hazards.', 89, 8, 2, '2013-11-08', NULL),
