(596, 3172, 'La revisión bibliográfica revela una acusada falta de datos de campo de tasas de erosión en campos agrícolas mediterráneos. Sin embargo, esa información es necesaria para llevar a cabo una correcta evaluación de la eficacia de las prácticas de conservación más adecuadas en este contexto\r\nagroambiental. En este trabajo se presenta el estudio de los efectos de un episodio erosivo extremo ocurrido sobre un campo agrícola en barbecho blanco, característico del secano mediterráneo. Con este objetivo se ha cartografiado con detalle una ladera afectada por una intensa reguerización, en la que se midieron más de 2500 secciones transversales de canales. Las tasas de erosión estimadas para cuatro microcuencas de drenaje arrojaron valores medios de 115.90 Mg ha-1, muy por encima de los valores máximos de pérdida tolerable de suelo (11.2 Mg ha-1 año-1, Schmidt et al., 1982), lo cual describe un episodio de erosión extrema. Sin embargo, el episodio erosivo se desencadeno a partir de una precipitación cuyo periodo de retorno se ha estimado en 5 años, lo que indica una frecuencia relativamente alta y en ningún caso un episodio erosivo extraordinario. De todo ello se concluye que debe considerarse este tipo de episodios, por su frecuencia y su potencial erosivo, como claves para seleccionar las prácticas de conservación más efectivas frente a la erosión hídrica en este contexto agroambiental. Así mismo, los resultados han mostrado la idoneidad del método\r\nde estudio desarrollado para ser aplicado de forma sistemática con el objetivo de crear bases de\r\ndatos que permitan evaluar adecuadamente la problemática existente.', 'es', 'The review of the literature reveals a defendant lack of field data rates of erosion in Mediterranean agricultural fields. However, such information is necessary to carry out a proper assessment of the effectiveness of more appropriate conservation practices in this context\r\nAgri-environment. This paper presents the study of the effects of an extreme erosion episode occurred on an agricultural field in fallow white, characteristic of the Mediterranean rainfed. With this aim, a slope affected by an intense reguerizacion, in which more than 2500 channels cross sections were measured has mapped in detail. Erosion rates estimated for four watershed drainage yielded mean values of 115.90 Mg ha-1, well above the maximum values of tolerable soil losses (11.2 Mg ha-1 year-1, Schmidt et al., 1982), which describes an episode of extreme erosion. However, the erosion episode unleashed from a precipitation whose return period has been estimated at 5 years, indicating a rate relatively high, and in any case an extraordinary erosion episode. This concludes that this type of episodes, should be considered by their frequency and erosive potential, as keys to select the most effective conservation practices against water erosion in this agri-environmental context. Likewise, the results have shown the suitability of the method\r\nstudy developed to be applied in a systematic manner with the aim of creating databases of\r\ndata allowing you to properly evaluate the existing problems.', 'en', 'The review of the literature reveals a defendant lack of field data rates of erosion in Mediterranean agricultural fields. However, such information is necessary to carry out a proper assessment of the effectiveness of more appropriate conservation practices in this agro-environmental context. This paper presents the study of the effects of an extreme erosion episode which occurred on an agricultural field in white fallow, characteristic of the Mediterranean rainfed. With this aim, a slope affected by an intense trailing, in which more than 2500 channels cross sections were mapped in details. Erosion rates estimated for four watershed drainage yielded mean values of 115.90 Mg ha-1, well above the maximum values of tolerable soil losses (11.2 Mg ha-1 year-1, Schmidt et al., 1982), which describes an episode of extreme erosion. However, the erosion episode unleashed from a precipitation whose return period has been estimated at 5 years, indicating a rate relatively high, and in any case an extraordinary erosion episode. This concludes that this type of episodes, should be considered by their frequency and erosive potential, as keys to select the most effective conservation practices against water erosion in this agro-environmental context. Likewise, the results have shown the suitability of the method study developed to be applied in a systematic manner with the aim of creating databases of data allowing you to properly evaluate the existing problems.', 23, 8, 2, '2013-11-13', NULL),
