(790, 3827, 'Efecto supresor de los extractos acuosos del compost obre la movilidad de zoosporas de pythium y phytophthora', 'es', 'Suppressive effect of aqueous extracts of compost do the mobility of zoospores of pythium and phytophthora', 'en', 'Suppressive effect of aqueous extracts of compost do the mobility of zoospores of pythium and phytophthora', 89, 6, 2, '2013-11-25', NULL),
(791, 3827, 'El empleo y desarrollo de distintos preparados basados en el compost y agua para\r\nel control de enfermedades, se encuentra en auge desde 1990 (Brinton, 1995; Diver, 2001). Son muchos los términos que se han empleado para estos preparados: té de compost, té de compost aireado, té orgánico, extractos de compost, extractos acuosos fermentados de compost, extracto enmendado, macerados de compost, y lodos líquidos de compost (algunos de ellos de difícil traducción al castellano). Muchos de los términos son sinónimos, mientras otros se prestan fácilmente a confundirse con otros conceptos (Scheuerell y Mahaffee, 2002).', 'es', 'The employment and development of different prepared compost and water-based for\r\nthe control of diseases, is booming since 1990 (Brinton, 1995;) Diver, 2001). There are many terms that have been used for these preparations: compost tea, tea of aerated compost, organic tea, compost, fermented aqueous extracts of compost extracts, extract amended, macerated compost, and compost liquid sludge (some of them difficult translation into Castilian). Many of the terms are synonymous, while others lend themselves easily to confused with other concepts (Scheuerell and Mahaffee, 2002).', 'en', 'The employment and development of different prepared compost and water-based for the control of diseases, is booming since 1990 (Brinton, 1995;) Diver, 2001). There are many terms that have been used for these preparations: compost tea, tea of aerated compost, organic tea, compost, fermented aqueous extracts of compost extracts, extract amended, macerated compost, and compost liquid sludge (some of them difficult translation into Castilian). Many of the terms are synonymous, while others lend themselves easily to confused with other concepts (Scheuerell and Mahaffee, 2002).', 89, 8, 2, '2013-11-25', NULL),
