(797, 3828, 'Se estudió la eficacia de la biofumigación para el control de Phytophthora capsici (PC), in vitro utilizando como material vegetal biofumigante hojas de pimiento, analizando dosis de material (75 y 100 g), sustrato empleado en el proceso (vermiculita esterilizada, compost de vid tratado térmicamente (6 días a 60ºC) y sin tratar, y tres\r\ntiempos de incubación (20, 30 y 40 días), realizándose tres repeticiones para cada tratamiento. En las condiciones del ensayo, se ha producido una reducción de la presencia de PC, dependiente de la dosis aplicada, el sustrato empleado y el tiempo de permanencia.', 'es', 'We studied the effectiveness of the biofumigation for control of Phytophthora capsici (PC), vitro used as plant material biofumigante pepper leaves, analyzing dose of material (75 and 100 g), used in the process substrate (sterile vermiculite, compost vine treated thermally (6 days at 60 ° C) and untreated, and three\r\n(20, 30 and 40 days) incubation times, making three replicates for each treatment. In the test conditions, a reduction in the presence of PC, dependent of the dose applied, the substrate used and time spent has occurred.', 'en', 'This paper studies the effectiveness of the biofumigation for control of Phytophthora capsici (PC), vitro used as plant material biofumigante pepper leaves, analyzing dose of material (75 and 100 g), used in the process substrate (sterile vermiculite, compost vine treated thermally (6 days at 60 ° C) and untreated, and three\r\n(20, 30 and 40 days) incubation times, making three replicates for each treatment. In the test conditions, a reduction in the presence of PC, dependent of the dose applied, the substrate used and time spent has occurred.', 89, 8, 2, '2013-11-25', NULL),
