(826, 3832, 'El melón es un cultivo tradicional de la comarca del Baix Vinalopó que forma parte de las rotaciones de cultivos. El uso de nuevas variedades, hace peligrar el abandono de las variedades tradicionales, siendo ésta una de las preocupaciones de organismos internacionales (FAO) por la perdida de parte del patrimonio genético y biodiversidad; fundamentos de la agricultura ecológica. Así mismo, resulta necesario conocer el comportamiento de las variedades autóctonas y compararlas en igualdad de condiciones de cultivo con otras variedades actuales (híbridos) de mayor implantación en la comarca. Siendo los objetivos del ensayo: comparar cinco variedades autóctonas de melón en cultivo ecológico con una variedad híbrida cultivada frecuentemente en la comarca.', 'es', 'The melon is a traditional crop of the region of the Baix Vinalopó which is part of the crop rotations. The use of new varieties, endangers the abandonment of traditional varieties, which is one of the concerns of international organisations (FAO) part of the genetic heritage and biodiversity loss; Fundamentals of organic farming. Likewise, it is necessary to know the behavior of the native varieties and compare them in equal conditions of cultivation with other current varieties (hybrids) greater implementation in the region. As the objectives of the trial: compare five native varieties of melon in organic farming with a hybrid variety commonly grown in the region.', 'en', 'The melon is a traditional crop of the region of the Baix Vinalopó which is part of the crop rotations. The use of new varieties, endangers the abandonment of traditional varieties, which is one of the concerns of international organisations (FAO) part of the genetic heritage and biodiversity loss; Fundamentals of organic farming. Likewise, it is necessary to know the behavior of the native varieties and compare them in equal conditions of cultivation with other current varieties (hybrids) greater implementation in the region. As the objectives of the trial: compare five native varieties of melon in organic farming with a hybrid variety commonly grown in the region.', 89, 8, 2, '2013-11-25', NULL),
