(995, 3861, 'Uno de los mayores problemas fitopatológicos del cultivo del tomate en las Islas\r\nCanarias son los nematodos formadores de nódulos del género Meloidogyne. En la\r\nbúsqueda de alternativas no químicas y de manejo para el control de los mismos, se analiza en este trabajo el efecto que tiene sobre un suelo de cultivo de tomates con infección natural de este patógeno la biofumigación en condiciones controladas utilizando restos de diferentes cultivos (pimiento, tomate y calabaza) convencionales y ecológicos, solos y en combinación con gallinaza.', 'es', 'One of the biggest problems phytopathological of the cultivation of tomato in the Islands\r\nCanary Islands are forming nematodes of the genus Meloidogyne nodules. In the\r\nsearch for non-chemical alternatives and management for control of the same, is analyzed in this work the effect that has on a floor of cultivation of tomatoes with natural infection of this pathogen the biofumigation under controlled conditions using remnants of different crops (tomato, pepper, squash) conventional and organic, alone and in combination with chicken manure.', 'en', 'One of the biggest problems phytopathological of the cultivation of tomato in the Canary Islands are forming nematodes of the genus Meloidogyne nodules. In the search for non-chemical alternatives and management for control of the same, is analyzed in this work the effect that has on a floor of cultivation of tomatoes with natural infection of this pathogen the biofumigation under controlled conditions using remnants of different crops (tomato, pepper, squash) conventional and organic, alone and in combination with chicken manure.', 89, 8, 2, '2013-12-02', NULL),
