(1113, 3881, 'Estudio comparativo del contenido en macro y micronutrientes en hortícolas cultivadas en invernadero con nutrición orgánica versus mineral', 'es', 'Comparative study of the content of macro and micro-nutrients in vegetables cultivated in greenhouse with organic versus mineral nutrition', 'en', 'Comparative study of the content of macro and micro-nutrients in vegetables cultivated in greenhouse with organic versus mineral nutrition', 89, 6, 2, '2013-12-03', NULL),
(1114, 3881, 'La agricultura ecológica tiene como uno de sus objetivos más importantes el obtener alimentos de alta calidad nutricional. En un experimento iniciado en 1995 y llevado a cabo en la finca del C.I.F.A Las Torres y Tomejil, de suelo franco, en el término municipal de Alcalá del Río (Sevilla), se han estudiado los contenidos en macro y micronutrientes de diferentes productos hortícolas cultivados en invernadero en parcelas nutridas orgánicamente en comparación con parcelas con nutrición mineral.\r\nEl estudio se ha centrado en el periodo 2001-2005, una vez sobrepasado el periodo de reconversión.', 'es', 'Organic farming has as one of its most important goals to get foods of high nutritional quality. In an experiment begun in 1995 and carried out on the farm of the C.I.F.A Las Torres and Tomejil, of soil, in the municipality of Alcalá del Río (Sevilla), we have studied the contents in macro and micro-nutrients of different horticultural products grown in greenhouse in plots nurtured organically compared with plots with mineral nutrition.\r\nThe study has focused on the period 2001-2005, once exceeded the conversion period.', 'en', 'Organic farming has as one of its most important goals to get foods of high nutritional quality. In an experiment begun in 1995 and carried out on the farm of the C.I.F.A Las Torres and Tomejil, of soil, in the municipality of Alcalá del Río (Sevilla), we have studied the contents in macro and micro-nutrients of different horticultural products grown in greenhouse in plots nurtured organically compared with plots with mineral nutrition.\r\nThe study has focused on the period 2001-2005, once exceeded the conversion period.', 89, 8, 2, '2013-12-03', NULL),
