(1361, 3929, 'Amarilleo necrótico de la judía: una enfermedad preocupante a diagnóstico ', 'es', 'Necrotic yellowing of the Jewish: a troubling disease diagnosis ', 'en', 'Necrotic yellowing of the beans: a troubling disease diagnosis ', 89, 6, 2, '2013-12-16', NULL),
(1362, 3929, 'En noviembre de 2003 hace su aparición en el sureste español una nueva enfermedad afectando al cultivo de judía (Phaseolus vulgaris L.) mostrando una sintomatología hasta entonces desconocida caracterizada por amarilleos internerviales en hojas que evolucionan a manchas cloróticas definidas y zonas necrosadas adquiriendo en un último estado tonalidades marrones, manteniendo los nervios verdes.', 'es', 'In November 2003 makes its appearance in the Southeast Spanish a new disease affecting Jewish culture (Phaseolus vulgaris l.) showing a hitherto unknown symptoms characterized by internerviales amarilleos in leaves that develop into well defined chlorotic spots and areas necrotic acquiring in a last State brown tones, keeping green nerves.', 'en', 'In November 2003 makes its appearance in the Southeast Spanish a new disease affecting cultivation of bean (Phaseolus vulgaris l.) showing a hitherto unknown symptoms characterized by internerviales amarilleos in leaves that develop into well defined chlorotic spots and areas necrotic acquiring in a last State brown tones, keeping green nerves.', 89, 8, 2, '2013-12-16', NULL),
