(1774, 4016, 'Los modelos de certificación participativos en latinoamérica como estrategia de certificación alternativa para el desarrollo de los mercados locales de agricultura orgánica', 'es', 'Participatory models of certification in Latin America as a strategy for alternative certification for the development of local markets for organic agriculture', 'en', 'Participatory models of certification in Latin America as a strategy for alternative certification for the development of local markets for organic agriculture', 89, 6, 2, '2014-01-09', NULL),
(1775, 4016, 'El modelo comercial de los productos ecológicos, originariamente diferenciado del de los productos de la agricultura convencional, ha evolucionado de forma que: el acceso a los mercados por parte de los pequeños agricultores es cada día mas complicado y la “certificación de tercera parte” resulta cara e inadecuada para determinadas situaciones regionales o locales, lo que hacen necesarios nuevos modelos que resuelvan esta problemática y faciliten la viabilidad de la agricultura familiar.', 'es', 'The business model of organic products, originally differed from the conventional agriculture products, has evolved in a way that: access to markets by small farmers is becoming more complicated and ', 'en', 'The business model of organic products, originally differed from the conventional agriculture products, has evolved in a way that: access to markets by small farmers is becoming more complicated and &quot;third party certification&quot; is expensive and unsuitable for certain regional or local situations that make necessary new models that solve this problem and facilitate the viability of family farming.', 89, 8, 2, '2014-01-09', NULL),
