(1820, 4028, 'Por producción ecológica, orgánica o biológica - certificada - se entiende, formalmente, a toda aquella producción donde se haya efectuado un proceso de certificación que revele que sus métodos productivos contribuyen al mantenimiento o mejoramiento de la fertilidad del suelo, y de la vida vegetal y animal, sin usar insumos sintéticos en la producción y en los procesos de transformación y comercio, por lo que se deriva que sus productos y subproductos son saludables para el consumo en general.', 'es', '-Certified - organic, organic or biological production means, formally, to all that production where a certification process that will reveal that their production methods contribute to the maintenance or improvement of fertility of the soil, and the plant and animal life, without the use of synthetic inputs in production and processes of transformation and trade, so it is derived that their products and by-products are healthy for consumption in general has been made.', 'en', '-Certified - organic, organic or biological production means, formally, to all that production where a certification process that will reveal that their production methods contribute to the maintenance or improvement of fertility of the soil, and the plant and animal life, without the use of synthetic inputs in production and processes of transformation and trade, so it is derived that their products and by-products are healthy for consumption in general has been made.', 89, 8, 2, '2014-01-10', NULL),
